heaviest_rainfall.status: 36.8mm of rain was recorded as having fallen on 04 January 2025, marking an exceptional 37.2 hour precipitation event.  At times the rain was falling at 4.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today ranked 5th for the heaviest rainfall ever in our records, with a peak intensity of 11.8mm per hour sustained for 2.1 hours, resulting in a total accumulation of 7.28mm.  A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 27.0mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.

longest_rain.status: The record duration for continuous rain was set on 04 January 2025, the storm lasted 37.2 hours with a total precipitation of 36.8mm and it reached 4.6mm per hour at times.

summary.description:
Today, a bit warmer for the feels like temperature (up 3.0°C) and outside temperature (up 2.2°C), more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 13%), and drier conditions in rainfall (down 0.3 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in rainfall (up 0.3 mm) and cloud levels (up 1064 m).

The past week and month had observable variation in rainfall (down 0.1 mm), cloud levels (up 1177 m), and light levels (up 2628 lux) when compared to today.
